===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:Paracelsus|Paracelsus]] for a tincture he made containing opium, from {{etyl|NL.|en}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|laudare||to praise}}, or {{m|la|ladanum||a gum resin}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|λάδανον|}}. Originally the same word as {{m|en|ladanum}}, {{m|en|ladbdanum}}, compare French {{m|fr|laudanum}}, Italian {{m|it|laudano}}, {{m|it|ladano}}. See {{m|en|ladanum}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# A [[tincture]] of [[opium]], once widely used for various [[medical]] purposes and as a [[recreational drug]].

